Get default equations of each type.

Source: R/allo_find.R
allo_find.Rd

Get default equations of each type.

allo_find(dbh_species)

Arguments

dbh_species

A dataframe as those created with add_species().

Value

A nested dataframe with each row containing the data of an equation type.

See also

Other functions to manipulate equations: add_equations, allo_evaluate, allo_lookup, allo_order

Examples

census <- fgeo.biomass::scbi_tree1
species <- fgeo.biomass::scbi_species
dbh_species <- add_species(
  census, species,
  site = "scbi"
)

allo_find(dbh_species)
#> # A tibble: 5 x 2
#>   eqn_type       data                 
#>   <chr>          <list>               
#> 1 species        <tibble [8,930 × 7]> 
#> 2 genus          <tibble [5,642 × 7]> 
#> 3 mixed_hardwood <tibble [5,516 × 7]> 
#> 4 family         <tibble [10,141 × 7]>
#> 5 woody_species  <tibble [0 × 7]>
